summary: This document is an FBI evidence receipt form (FD-340) and accompanying materials related to a subpoena to MySpace.com. It includes the receipt for original interview notes and the results of the MySpace subpoena for specific user IDs, showing account and IP activity information for users in West Palm Beach, Florida, dated March 1, 2007.

persons.name: Ply Stitt
persons.context: Listed as the name of the contributor/interviewee on the FD-340 evidence receipt form, suggesting they provided the original interview notes.

persons.name: Ceiting Lu
persons.context: Signed the cover letter from MySpace.com transmitting the subpoena results to the FBI Special Agent in West Palm Beach.

events.title: MySpace Subpoena Results Transmitted
events.description: MySpace.com sends the results of a subpoena for specific user IDs to the FBI in West Palm Beach via fax and UPS.

events.title: MySpace Account Creation

events.title: MySpace Account Creation

keyFacts: The FBI received original interview notes from an individual named Ply Stitt as part of an investigation.
MySpace.com complied with a subpoena, providing account and IP activity data for four specific user IDs (60688973, 65739018, 65739759, 172831).
The MySpace accounts were created between 2003 and 2006, with several linked to West Palm Beach, Florida.
The document is marked as containing Grand Jury material, indicating it was part of a secret grand jury proceeding.
The evidence was formally received by the FBI on an unspecified date in 2007, as documented on an FD-340 form.
